reviews.text:
McDonald's has a way of having a pretty standardized menu all over the world (big Mac, nuggets etc) plus local twists.  It's a winning combination to attract audiences all over the world to their bread and butter menu plus a concession to local tastes.

Here I got the dipped strawberry (from Fukukoa) sundae cone $6.50, pretty decent on a cool day.
Can get some easy lunch there...
ACE it's not like home Mckie N it's a long way 2 try it yourself.
A little slow. Food tasted good 😋 . Ice cream great and cheap 8 $HK for Sunday.
if you need a beef burger fix it's just nearby
